11:46.600 --> 11:47.460
Did I screw up?

11:47.460 --> 11:57.460
And for the audience, so you're basically showing that the Earth's shadow would not, obviously, a solar reflection wouldn't show up there.

11:57.580 --> 11:57.840
Exactly.

11:58.160 --> 12:03.040
So a real object, you know, that was in the way of the sun, you would get a solar reflection.

12:03.560 --> 12:06.020
A non-real object, you wouldn't get anything, right?

12:06.100 --> 12:12.940
And so what you're showing is that these are real solar reflections because there is a deficit in the Earth's shadow of these objects.

12:12.940 --> 12:18.880
Exactly, because inside the Earth's shadow, if the sun doesn't reach, you're not going to get the reflection.

12:19.560 --> 12:22.900
While if you're outside the Earth's shadow, it's going to reflect sunlight.

12:22.980 --> 12:27.400
