24:49.740 --> 24:54.440
Our story begins in 1953, four years before Sputnik.

24:55.100 --> 24:59.660
Enter Major Donald Kehoe, a retired Marine Corps naval aviator

24:59.660 --> 25:03.120
and one of the earliest public advocates for UFO disclosure.

25:03.840 --> 25:05.760
Kehoe states something astonishing,

25:05.760 --> 25:10.260
that the Air Force was tracking two unknown artificial satellites,

25:10.740 --> 25:14.060
400 and 600 miles up in low Earth orbit.

25:14.500 --> 25:16.820
The timing here was likely not a coincidence.

25:17.640 --> 25:22.200
That same year, a very unusual project started at White Sands Missile Range,

25:22.880 --> 25:26.620
a military-funded initiative to track small natural satellites,

25:27.000 --> 25:28.900
think asteroids captured in orbit.

25:29.300 --> 25:31.560
Two remarkable scientists were in charge.

25:31.680 --> 25:34.860
First up is meteorite expert Dr. Lincoln LaPaz.

25:34.860 --> 25:39.100
Before joining this special search for mini-moons around Earth,

25:39.600 --> 25:41.820
Dr. LaPaz headed up Project Twinkle,

25:42.500 --> 25:46.340
an Air Force investigation into unexplained green fireballs

25:46.340 --> 25:48.960
showing up across American nuclear sites.

25:49.320 --> 25:53.040
Documented at places like Los Alamos and Holloman Air Force Base,

25:53.580 --> 25:56.840
LaPaz arrived at the conclusion that these green fireballs

25:56.840 --> 25:58.840
were not a known natural phenomenon,

25:59.160 --> 26:01.840
and they seemed to propel themselves intelligently.

26:01.840 --> 26:05.100
Second on the project, we have Clyde Tombaugh.

26:05.400 --> 26:09.060
Yes, that Clyde Tombaugh, the man who discovered Pluto.

26:09.580 --> 26:13.220
The man whose ashes are now speeding towards interstellar space

26:13.220 --> 26:16.160
inside the most expensive urn ever built,

26:16.740 --> 26:18.540
NASA's New Horizons spacecraft.

26:19.140 --> 26:20.560
Until the day he died,

26:20.980 --> 26:23.620
Tombaugh remained steadfast in his conviction

26:23.620 --> 26:27.820
that some UFOs could represent visiting alien spacecraft.

26:27.820 --> 26:29.660
So one has to wonder,

26:29.940 --> 26:32.180
given wild rumors from credible sources

26:32.180 --> 26:34.420
