26:34.680 --> 26:36.960
what exactly did they actually find?

26:37.200 --> 26:39.420
On August 23rd, 1954,

26:39.960 --> 26:43.920
Aviation Week and Space Technology published a statement from LaPaz,

26:44.520 --> 26:47.520
one which begged way more questions than it answered.

26:47.520 --> 26:52.520
LaPaz confirmed that there were indeed two unknown objects.

26:53.140 --> 26:56.760
But simultaneously, he claimed that the two unknown objects

26:56.760 --> 26:59.360
were fully identified natural asteroids

26:59.360 --> 27:01.800
caught in Earth's gravitational grasp.

27:02.120 --> 27:05.460
He might have been doing this to dispel American domestic panic

27:05.460 --> 27:07.460
that this could have been Soviet tech.

27:08.140 --> 27:09.780
But if you read between the lines,

27:09.940 --> 27:11.860
there's a lot that just doesn't add up.

27:12.100 --> 27:15.820
Firstly, these observations directly corroborate Kehoe's story.

27:15.820 --> 27:18.940
White Sands Missile Range actually was tracking

27:18.940 --> 27:21.580
two unidentified objects in low Earth orbit.

27:22.020 --> 27:25.200
