36:40.700 --> 36:41.780
And we kind of

36:41.780 --> 36:42.700
came up with the plan

36:42.700 --> 36:43.800
for how to do it

36:43.800 --> 36:44.820
and over the course

36:44.820 --> 36:45.860
of the past year,

36:46.300 --> 36:47.200
compiled this

36:47.200 --> 36:48.240
enormous database

36:48.240 --> 36:51.960
with 2,700 days

36:51.960 --> 36:52.340
in it.

36:52.400 --> 36:53.460
And for each day

36:53.460 --> 36:54.340
we recorded,

36:54.460 --> 36:55.200
was there a nuclear

36:55.200 --> 36:56.320
test that day?

36:56.820 --> 36:57.360
There were like

36:57.360 --> 36:59.080
134 over that

36:59.080 --> 36:59.840
period of time.

37:00.160 --> 37:01.060
Was there a transient

37:01.060 --> 37:02.540
that day?

37:02.860 --> 37:03.240
And there were

37:03.240 --> 37:04.420
transients were only

37:04.420 --> 37:05.320
seen on about

37:05.320 --> 37:06.740
300 days

37:06.740 --> 37:07.240
out of those

37:07.240 --> 37:08.160
2,700.

37:08.940 --> 37:10.020
And then we looked,

37:10.240 --> 37:11.200
is there a relationship

37:11.200 --> 37:12.320
between those

37:12.320 --> 37:13.620
and a relationship

37:13.620 --> 37:15.180
