37:15.180 --> 37:15.980
in the old

37:15.980 --> 37:17.820
Center for UFO Studies

37:17.820 --> 37:19.640
UFOCAT database,

37:19.820 --> 37:20.340
which covers

37:20.340 --> 37:21.380
that period of time.

37:21.880 --> 37:23.680
And, you know,

37:23.720 --> 37:24.500
I was shocked.

37:25.100 --> 37:26.400
We got a really

37:26.400 --> 37:27.500
interesting finding

37:27.500 --> 37:28.500
that was highly

37:28.500 --> 37:30.020
significant statistically.

37:30.980 --> 37:33.000
And I double-checked

37:33.000 --> 37:33.960
it, triple-checked

37:33.960 --> 37:34.900
it, and then reached

37:34.900 --> 37:35.700
out to Beatrice.

37:35.860 --> 37:37.000
She was very excited.

37:37.120 --> 37:37.760
And we immediately

37:37.760 --> 37:39.120
