37:43.480 --> 37:45.080
called Scientific Reports.

37:45.820 --> 37:46.360
That's amazing.

37:46.540 --> 37:47.140
Congratulations.

37:47.660 --> 37:49.140
So, how strong

37:49.140 --> 37:49.720
is the correlation

37:49.720 --> 37:50.520
that you found

37:50.520 --> 37:51.600
between the transients

37:51.600 --> 37:53.340
and nuclear tests?

37:53.660 --> 37:54.520
Let me put that

37:54.520 --> 37:55.180
two ways.

37:55.340 --> 37:56.240
So, statistically,

37:56.920 --> 37:58.340
there is an

37:58.340 --> 38:00.140
8 in 1,000 chance

38:00.140 --> 38:01.200
that this is an error,

38:01.920 --> 38:02.680
which means

38:02.680 --> 38:03.660
it's pretty unlikely

38:03.660 --> 38:04.440
that it's an error.

38:05.440 --> 38:06.460
And then the other

38:06.460 --> 38:07.260
way to look at it

38:07.260 --> 38:08.540
is in terms of percentages.

38:09.020 --> 38:09.760
So, out of those

38:09.760 --> 38:10.920
2,700,

38:11.140 --> 38:11.700
days,

38:11.920 --> 38:12.900
if there's no

38:12.900 --> 38:13.920
nuclear test,

38:14.100 --> 38:14.880
there's a transient

38:14.880 --> 38:16.860
on 11% of those days.

38:17.240 --> 38:17.940
But if there's been

38:17.940 --> 38:19.260
a nuclear test

38:19.260 --> 38:20.180
the day before,

38:21.020 --> 38:21.620
then it's

38:21.620 --> 38:23.120
almost 19%

38:23.120 --> 38:23.820
of those days

38:23.820 --> 38:24.500
have a transient.

38:24.920 --> 38:26.060
So, that 11%

38:26.060 --> 38:27.080
versus 19%

38:27.080 --> 38:28.700
is about

38:28.700 --> 38:29.920
a 68%

38:29.920 --> 38:30.740
increase

38:30.740 --> 38:31.240
in risk

38:31.240 --> 38:31.980
for a transient

38:31.980 --> 38:32.600
if you've had

38:32.600 --> 38:33.680
a nuclear test.

38:34.340 --> 38:34.580
And so,

38:34.760 --> 38:36.000
when you're

38:36.000 --> 38:36.740
documenting

38:36.740 --> 38:38.000
all these nuclear tests,

38:38.180 --> 38:38.880
these are tests

38:38.880 --> 38:39.440
presumably

38:39.440 --> 38:40.080
at the Nevada

38:40.080 --> 38:40.840
test site,

38:41.040 --> 38:41.600
which turned

38:41.600 --> 38:42.640
into Area 51,

38:43.460 --> 38:44.780
maybe the Marshall Islands,

38:45.160 --> 38:46.300
like those sorts

38:46.300 --> 38:47.220
of nuclear tests,

38:47.420 --> 38:47.680
and then,

38:47.720 --> 38:47.880
you know,

38:47.920 --> 38:48.440
maybe whatever

38:48.440 --> 38:49.400
Russia was doing

38:49.400 --> 38:50.180
with the Tsar bomb

38:50.180 --> 38:51.100
in Kazakhstan,

38:51.480 --> 38:52.000
that sort of thing.

38:52.000 --> 38:54.240
that is all true.

38:54.340 --> 38:54.980
It's Kazakhstan,

38:55.360 --> 38:55.720
there's some

38:55.720 --> 38:56.500
British tests

38:56.500 --> 38:57.340
in Australia,

38:57.720 --> 38:59.300
and then the U.S.

38:59.360 --> 39:00.400
tests in New Mexico

39:00.400 --> 39:01.420
and in the Pacific.

39:02.180 --> 39:02.620
That's right,

39:02.700 --> 39:03.380
there's WUMERA

39:03.380 --> 39:04.180
test range,

39:04.340 --> 39:04.540
which

39:04.540 --> 39:06.500
the head of the

39:06.500 --> 39:07.180
nuclear division

39:07.180 --> 39:08.260
actually in Australia,

39:08.520 --> 39:09.660
the joint intelligence

39:09.660 --> 39:10.400
organization,

39:10.400 --> 39:11.180
was a guy named

39:11.180 --> 39:11.740
Harry Turner,

39:12.000 --> 39:13.080
