41:11.600 --> 41:13.880
And I have to say,

41:14.160 --> 41:15.980
a few years ago,

41:15.980 --> 41:16.520
I would think

41:16.520 --> 41:17.180
I was crazy

41:17.180 --> 41:18.120
for saying this,

41:18.460 --> 41:19.840
but these are just

41:19.840 --> 41:21.040
statistical facts.

41:21.300 --> 41:22.580
So Beatrice has shown

41:22.580 --> 41:25.260
that these transients,

41:25.600 --> 41:26.800
the number of transients

41:26.800 --> 41:28.020
drops dramatically

41:28.020 --> 41:29.560
when they are in an area

41:29.560 --> 41:30.540
where the Earth's shadow

41:30.540 --> 41:31.020
would be.

41:31.280 --> 41:32.380
So that indicates

41:32.380 --> 41:33.500
that they are reflective

41:33.500 --> 41:34.520
objects in orbit.

41:34.800 --> 41:36.080
They're not plate defects.

41:37.280 --> 41:39.100
Our findings indicate

41:39.100 --> 41:41.760
that these things

41:41.760 --> 41:44.600
were in the sky

41:44.600 --> 41:46.560
the day after

41:46.560 --> 41:47.600
a nuclear test,

41:47.900 --> 41:48.740
and they weren't there

41:48.740 --> 41:49.500
the day before.

41:50.080 --> 41:51.360
So somehow,

41:51.700 --> 41:53.020
based on a nuclear test

41:53.020 --> 41:53.660
going off,

41:53.700 --> 41:54.940
within 24 hours,

41:55.180 --> 41:56.400
you have these objects,

41:56.560 --> 41:57.300
whatever they are,

41:57.460 --> 41:58.380
appearing in

41:58.380 --> 41:59.400
geosynchronous orbit.

42:00.000 --> 42:00.380
Now,

42:00.720 --> 42:01.960
who is behind that?

42:02.320 --> 42:02.500
You know,

42:02.540 --> 42:03.920
where did these come from,

42:03.960 --> 42:05.040
and how can they be

42:05.040 --> 42:05.840
