53:36.840 --> 53:47.900
In 1961, legendary

53:47.900 --> 53:49.500
astronomer Frank Drake

53:49.500 --> 53:50.840
started Project

53:50.840 --> 53:52.380
OSMA, the first

53:52.380 --> 53:53.680
ever organized search

53:53.680 --> 53:55.060
for interstellar radio

53:55.060 --> 53:55.620
signals.

53:56.400 --> 53:57.900
Drake scrounged

53:57.900 --> 53:58.980
together an antenna

53:58.980 --> 54:00.360
and dish using

54:00.360 --> 54:01.840
scrapped radar parts

54:01.840 --> 54:02.860
from World War II,

54:03.020 --> 54:03.900
and pointed the whole

54:03.900 --> 54:05.460
apparatus skywards in

54:05.460 --> 54:06.660
hopes of intercepting

54:06.660 --> 54:07.180
an alien

54:07.180 --> 54:07.820
transmission.

54:09.000 --> 54:10.540
In doing so, he

54:10.540 --> 54:11.620
initiated the largest

54:11.620 --> 54:12.560
scale search for

54:12.560 --> 54:13.700
intelligent life our

54:13.700 --> 54:14.960
astronomical community

54:14.960 --> 54:16.300
has ever engaged in.

54:17.760 --> 54:18.780
SETI, or the

54:18.780 --> 54:19.240
Search for

54:19.240 --> 54:20.080
Extraterrestrial

54:20.080 --> 54:21.260
Intelligence, had

54:21.260 --> 54:22.720
begun its 70-plus

54:22.720 --> 54:23.440
year life.

54:24.000 --> 54:25.180
Outside of a few

54:25.180 --> 54:26.540
unresolvable blips,

54:26.780 --> 54:27.500
like the famous

54:27.500 --> 54:28.740
wow signal discovered

54:28.740 --> 54:30.000
by Jerry Amon at

54:30.000 --> 54:31.900
Ohio State, no alien

54:31.900 --> 54:32.960
radio signals have

54:32.960 --> 54:34.400
ever been detected in

54:34.400 --> 54:35.140
a repeatable,

54:35.300 --> 54:36.160
consistent way.

54:36.620 --> 54:37.580
Nonetheless, the

54:37.580 --> 54:38.620
search is still in

54:38.620 --> 54:39.340
its infancy.

54:39.920 --> 54:40.940
One study literally

54:40.940 --> 54:42.040
calculated that the

54:42.040 --> 54:43.260
volume of the galaxy

54:43.260 --> 54:44.500
that SETI has scanned

54:44.500 --> 54:45.960
so far is like

54:45.960 --> 54:46.960
comparing the volume

54:46.960 --> 54:48.320
of a hot tub of water

54:48.320 --> 54:49.500
to all of the Earth's

54:49.500 --> 54:50.820
oceans and asking,

54:51.340 --> 54:52.220
where are all of the

54:52.220 --> 54:52.560
fish?

54:52.560 --> 54:59.820
Even back in the

54:59.820 --> 55:00.960
early 60s, at the

55:00.960 --> 55:02.460
start of SETI, some

55:02.460 --> 55:03.180
of its scientists

55:03.180 --> 55:04.700
were already exploring

55:04.700 --> 55:05.920
radical alternative

55:05.920 --> 55:07.440
possibilities, even

55:07.440 --> 55:08.560
ones that went far

55:08.560 --> 55:09.700
beyond basic radio

55:09.700 --> 55:10.220
signals.

55:11.300 --> 55:13.340
One such outside-the-box

55:13.340 --> 55:14.580
thinker was electrical

55:14.580 --> 55:16.580
engineer Ronald Bracewell

55:16.580 --> 55:18.340
and his concept of a

55:18.340 --> 55:19.580
communicating probe.

55:19.580 --> 55:21.940
Let's say you're

55:21.940 --> 55:22.700
trying to have a

55:22.700 --> 55:23.380
phone call with

55:23.380 --> 55:24.600
alien broadcasters

55:24.600 --> 55:26.140
in Epsilon Botees,

55:26.400 --> 55:27.880
some 203 light

55:27.880 --> 55:28.460
years away.

55:29.140 --> 55:30.040
You send a message,

55:30.320 --> 55:31.100
hey, what's up?

55:32.120 --> 55:33.540
406 years after you

55:33.540 --> 55:34.260
sent the original

55:34.260 --> 55:35.460
message, comes the

55:35.460 --> 55:36.620
response, nothing

55:36.620 --> 55:37.740
much, how about

55:37.740 --> 55:38.040
you?

55:38.420 --> 55:39.300
The point is, it

55:39.300 --> 55:40.660
would take 406

55:40.660 --> 55:41.840
years just to

55:41.840 --> 55:43.140
exchange those two

55:43.140 --> 55:43.640
sentences.

55:44.380 --> 55:45.260
Interstellar radio

55:45.260 --> 55:46.620
beacons don't exactly

55:46.620 --> 55:47.580
make for engaging

55:47.580 --> 55:48.920
real-time conversation.

55:48.920 --> 55:50.280
The speed of light is

55:50.280 --> 55:51.240
the fastest thing we

55:51.240 --> 55:52.380
know, but it's also

55:52.380 --> 55:53.400
painfully slow.

55:53.880 --> 55:54.900
Here's where Bracewell

55:54.900 --> 55:55.900
saw an intriguing

55:55.900 --> 55:56.580
concept.

55:56.860 --> 55:57.660
Instead of waiting

55:57.660 --> 55:58.740
around for radio

55:58.740 --> 55:59.680
signals to cross

55:59.680 --> 56:00.840
interstellar distances,

56:01.420 --> 56:02.620
why not send a

56:02.620 --> 56:04.000
physical robotic probe

56:04.000 --> 56:05.040
to the star system

56:05.040 --> 56:05.700
of interest?

56:06.000 --> 56:06.900
Even if you couldn't

56:06.900 --> 56:07.720
have a real-time

56:07.720 --> 56:08.700
conversation with

56:08.700 --> 56:09.540
someone from another

56:09.540 --> 56:10.640
star, you could

56:10.640 --> 56:11.860
upload an automated

56:11.860 --> 56:13.320
messaging system, or

56:13.320 --> 56:14.460
even eventually your

56:14.460 --> 56:15.840
mind, into an

56:15.840 --> 56:16.960
interstellar spacecraft,

56:17.540 --> 56:18.300
which could then,

56:18.300 --> 56:19.680
upon arriving in orbit

56:19.680 --> 56:20.620
of the destination

56:20.620 --> 56:22.440
planet, after eons in

56:22.440 --> 56:23.920
the void, initiate a

56:23.920 --> 56:25.140
real-time conversation

56:25.140 --> 56:25.940
with the local

56:25.940 --> 56:26.760
lifeforms.

56:26.760 --> 56:30.380
But what would the

56:30.380 --> 56:31.400
first message be?

56:31.640 --> 56:32.820
How would one even go

56:32.820 --> 56:34.080
about starting such an

56:34.080 --> 56:35.280
interspecies dialogue?

56:35.760 --> 56:36.840
Bracewell's idea was

56:36.840 --> 56:37.180
simple.

56:37.680 --> 56:38.820
You'd intercept whatever

56:38.820 --> 56:40.240
radio transmissions the

56:40.240 --> 56:41.100
locals were already

56:41.100 --> 56:42.680
sending out, and then

56:42.680 --> 56:43.840
send those radio

56:43.840 --> 56:45.220
transmissions back to

56:45.220 --> 56:45.460
them.

56:45.460 --> 56:47.160
Bracewell took his

56:47.160 --> 56:48.400
speculation one step

56:48.400 --> 56:49.980
further by considering

56:49.980 --> 56:51.320
that such a probe may

56:51.320 --> 56:52.960
already be lurking

56:52.960 --> 56:54.060
somewhere in the dark

56:54.060 --> 56:55.340
recesses of our solar

56:55.340 --> 56:57.060
system, waiting to reach

56:57.060 --> 56:58.260
out at any moment.

57:03.260 --> 57:04.800
One may recall a

57:04.800 --> 57:06.060
relevant scene in Carl

57:06.060 --> 57:07.280
Sagan's classic novel

57:07.280 --> 57:08.860
Contact, which follows

57:08.860 --> 57:10.220
SETI astronomer Ellie

57:10.220 --> 57:12.380
Arroway as she intercepts a

57:12.380 --> 57:13.680
genuine extraterrestrial

57:13.680 --> 57:15.660
signal sent from aliens in

57:15.660 --> 57:16.840
the Vega star system.

57:18.160 --> 57:20.420
In a wild plot twist, the

57:20.420 --> 57:21.820
initial contents of the

57:21.820 --> 57:23.820
message come as some shock.

57:24.240 --> 57:25.380
Hitler's speech at the

57:25.380 --> 57:27.640
1936 Olympics was Earth's

57:27.640 --> 57:28.780
first-ever television

57:28.780 --> 57:30.080
broadcast to break through

57:30.080 --> 57:31.420
the ionosphere and reach

57:31.420 --> 57:31.900
space.

57:33.260 --> 57:35.360
So in the novel, Hitler is

57:35.360 --> 57:36.900
also the first representative

57:36.900 --> 57:38.300
of humanity the Vega

57:38.300 --> 57:39.560
civilization sees.

57:39.800 --> 57:41.080
Not exactly a good first

57:41.080 --> 57:41.440
look.

57:44.860 --> 57:45.980
In a manner just like

57:45.980 --> 57:47.780
Bracewell's concept, the

57:47.780 --> 57:49.360
Vega aliens decide to

57:49.360 --> 57:50.640
respond by bouncing

57:50.640 --> 57:52.320
Hitler's speech back to its

57:52.320 --> 57:54.180
initial source, encoding

57:54.180 --> 57:55.940
instructions inside of it to

57:55.940 --> 57:57.240
build an interstellar

57:57.240 --> 57:58.180
wormhole device.

57:58.180 --> 58:08.480
It's worth remembering that the

58:08.480 --> 58:10.040
solar system is a very big

58:10.040 --> 58:10.480
place.

58:10.980 --> 58:12.440
It's also a very ancient

58:12.440 --> 58:12.940
place.

58:13.440 --> 58:14.820
Given the vastness of space

58:14.820 --> 58:16.220
and time in our solar system

58:16.220 --> 58:18.080
alone, where would any such a

58:18.080 --> 58:19.020
probe park itself?

58:19.660 --> 58:21.000
The Earth-Moon Lagrange

58:21.000 --> 58:22.600
points would be the ideal

58:22.600 --> 58:23.140
choice.

58:24.460 --> 58:26.300
Think of Lagrange points as

58:26.300 --> 58:28.220
pockets of stability, where

58:28.220 --> 58:30.140
gravity, rotation, and orbital

58:30.140 --> 58:32.620
motion all balance out, and

58:32.620 --> 58:34.340
objects within these pockets

58:34.340 --> 58:35.420
stay still.

58:36.200 --> 58:37.800
If our solar system truly is

58:37.800 --> 58:39.860
awash in alien time capsules and

58:39.860 --> 58:41.620
artifacts, they'd accumulate in

58:41.620 --> 58:43.280
Lagrange points, like a grand

58:43.280 --> 58:44.880
celestial treasure chest for

58:44.880 --> 58:46.520
space-bound archaeologists.

58:46.680 --> 58:48.460
If you wanted to send a probe to

58:48.460 --> 58:50.540
monitor our planet for millions or

58:50.540 --> 58:53.080
even billions of years, the Lagrange

58:53.080 --> 58:54.820
points are a great strategy for

58:54.820 --> 58:56.380
playing such an observational

58:56.380 --> 58:56.940
long game.

58:58.240 --> 58:59.900
Okay, but Jesse, isn't this

58:59.900 --> 59:01.640
episode supposed to be all about

59:01.640 --> 59:02.360
hard data?

59:02.640 --> 59:04.020
Why all the sci-fi speculation?

59:04.580 --> 59:06.640
Well, it so happens there's a

59:06.640 --> 59:08.880
long, well-documented, unexplained

59:08.880 --> 59:11.120
radio phenomenon that eerily

59:11.120 --> 59:13.140
pattern matches to many of these

59:13.140 --> 59:14.340
ideas and predictions.

59:14.980 --> 59:16.800
I'm talking about long-delay

59:16.800 --> 59:18.560
echoes, or LDEs.

59:18.940 --> 59:21.240
The story begins back in 1927.

59:21.920 --> 59:23.560
Norwegian shortwave radio

59:23.560 --> 59:25.120
radio operators began to notice

59:25.120 --> 59:26.020
something odd.

59:29.020 --> 59:31.260
Shortwave radio naturally travels

59:31.260 --> 59:32.900
around the world and makes its way

59:32.900 --> 59:35.240
back to its source, usually creating

59:35.240 --> 59:37.120
an echo one-seventh of a second

59:37.120 --> 59:38.500
after the initial signal.

59:38.840 --> 59:40.300
This is completely normal and

59:40.300 --> 59:40.760
expected.

59:41.220 --> 59:43.400
One-seventh of a second is how long

59:43.400 --> 59:45.180
it takes to travel around the entire

59:45.180 --> 59:47.020
Earth's circumference at the speed of

59:47.020 --> 59:47.260
light.

59:47.600 --> 59:49.660
Radio waves, of course, travel at the

59:49.660 --> 59:50.260
speed of light.

59:50.260 --> 59:52.840
But for some transmissions, a ghostly

59:52.840 --> 59:57.680
echo would follow, sometimes up to 30

59:57.680 --> 59:58.580
seconds later.

59:59.380 --> 01:00:01.820
Much too late to be a normal shortwave

01:00:01.820 --> 01:00:02.540
radio echo.

01:00:03.400 --> 01:00:05.580
The radio operators who first noticed

01:00:05.580 --> 01:00:07.900
this phenomenon were completely baffled.

01:00:08.300 --> 01:00:10.840
Norwegian physicist Carl Stormer quickly

01:00:10.840 --> 01:00:13.040
got to work trying to explain these

01:00:13.040 --> 01:00:14.080
mysterious echoes.

01:00:14.660 --> 01:00:16.700
To this day, a definitive answer

01:00:16.700 --> 01:00:17.760
remains elusive.

01:00:20.660 --> 01:00:23.640
A vast majority of LDEs are likely

01:00:23.640 --> 01:00:25.740
caused by radio waves bouncing through

01:00:25.740 --> 01:00:27.380
plasma in Earth's ionosphere.

01:00:29.380 --> 01:00:32.920
A few are more mysterious, perhaps even

01:00:32.920 --> 01:00:34.820
echoing from the Earth-Moon Lagrange

01:00:34.820 --> 01:00:35.240
points.

01:00:35.680 --> 01:00:37.960
Some of the longer delay times match the

01:00:37.960 --> 01:00:40.140
travel time to these Lagrange points.

01:00:40.140 --> 01:00:43.340
And one study even found a statistically

01:00:43.340 --> 01:00:46.480
significant increase in LDEs when the

01:00:46.480 --> 01:00:48.980
Earth-Moon L5 Lagrange point was above

01:00:48.980 --> 01:00:49.700
the horizon.

01:00:50.240 --> 01:00:52.400
Just consider for a moment how closely

01:00:52.400 --> 01:00:54.720
long delay echoes resemble Bracewell's

01:00:54.720 --> 01:00:56.760
concept for interstellar communication,

01:00:57.140 --> 01:00:59.080
taking local transmissions and bouncing

01:00:59.080 --> 01:00:59.700
them back.

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:02.440
This, coupled with a possible origin in

01:01:02.440 --> 01:01:05.060
Earth-Moon Lagrange points, paints a picture

01:01:05.060 --> 01:01:07.520
eerily similar to the long hypothesized

01:01:07.520 --> 01:01:10.340
notions of what contact could look like.

01:01:11.900 --> 01:01:14.680
Could some of these echoing Bracewell probes

01:01:14.680 --> 01:01:16.980
be what Beatrice has detected on the

01:01:16.980 --> 01:01:17.780
Palomar plates?

