show up in

01:14:06.420 --> 01:14:07.320
polar orbits.

01:14:07.920 --> 01:14:08.900
In a polar orbit,

01:14:09.280 --> 01:14:09.800
the satellite

01:14:09.800 --> 01:14:10.940
passes directly

01:14:10.940 --> 01:14:11.500
over the

01:14:11.500 --> 01:14:11.980
North and

01:14:11.980 --> 01:14:12.640
South Pole,

01:14:13.240 --> 01:14:13.840
making it the

01:14:13.840 --> 01:14:14.620
only orbit

01:14:14.620 --> 01:14:15.400
capable of

01:14:15.400 --> 01:14:16.020
imaging the

01:14:16.020 --> 01:14:16.940
entire Earth's

01:14:16.940 --> 01:14:17.860
surface as the

01:14:17.860 --> 01:14:18.580
planet turns

01:14:18.580 --> 01:14:18.980
below.

01:14:19.480 --> 01:14:20.220
In other words,

01:14:20.360 --> 01:14:21.120
if these objects

01:14:21.120 --> 01:14:22.180
were indeed from

01:14:22.180 --> 01:14:23.280
an alien civilization,

01:14:23.700 --> 01:14:24.040
they would have

01:14:24.040 --> 01:14:24.800
been peering down

01:14:24.800 --> 01:14:25.640
from a perfect

01:14:25.640 --> 01:14:26.860
vantage point to

01:14:26.860 --> 01:14:27.760
survey the Earth.

01:14:28.160 --> 01:14:29.060
Some try to

01:14:29.060 --> 01:14:29.760
explain away

01:14:29.760 --> 01:14:30.560
Jacques' orbital

01:14:30.560 --> 01:14:31.500
mystery sighting

01:14:31.500 --> 01:14:32.160
by invoking

01:14:32.160 --> 01:14:32.780
the Corona

01:14:32.780 --> 01:14:34.080
program, a

01:14:34.080 --> 01:14:34.760
series of

01:14:34.760 --> 01:14:35.660
highly secretive

01:14:35.660 --> 01:14:36.660
CIA-sponsored

01:14:36.660 --> 01:14:37.660
satellites first

01:14:37.660 --> 01:14:38.340
launched in

01:14:38.340 --> 01:14:39.840
1960, kicking

01:14:39.840 --> 01:14:40.660
off the modern

01:14:40.660 --> 01:14:41.600
era of orbital

01:14:41.600 --> 01:14:42.420
espionage.

01:14:42.860 --> 01:14:43.300
The Corona

01:14:43.300 --> 01:14:44.240
satellites did

01:14:44.240 --> 01:14:44.960
have a nearly

01:14:44.960 --> 01:14:45.720
polar orbit.

01:14:46.100 --> 01:14:46.900
However, it's a

01:14:46.900 --> 01:14:47.740
very insufficient

01:14:47.740 --> 01:14:48.480
explanation.

01:14:48.980 --> 01:14:49.800
As Vallée pointed

01:14:49.800 --> 01:14:50.620
out in a later

01:14:50.620 --> 01:14:51.080
interview,

01:14:51.520 --> 01:14:52.640
Later, I found

01:14:52.640 --> 01:14:53.460
out that other

01:14:53.460 --> 01:14:54.600
observatories had

01:14:54.600 --> 01:14:55.740
made exactly the

01:14:55.740 --> 01:14:56.700
same observation,

01:14:57.300 --> 01:14:58.080
and that in fact

01:14:58.080 --> 01:14:59.100
American tracking

01:14:59.100 --> 01:14:59.960
stations had

01:14:59.960 --> 01:15:00.900
photographed the

01:15:00.900 --> 01:15:01.960
same thing and

01:15:01.960 --> 01:15:02.820
couldn't identify

01:15:02.820 --> 01:15:03.380
it either.

01:15:03.740 --> 01:15:04.540
It was as bright

01:15:04.540 --> 01:15:05.360
as the star

01:15:05.360 --> 01:15:06.020
Sirius.

01:15:06.420 --> 01:15:06.960
You couldn't

01:15:06.960 --> 01:15:07.420
miss it.

01:15:07.740 --> 01:15:08.880
It didn't reappear

01:15:08.880 --> 01:15:09.640
in successive

01:15:09.640 --> 01:15:10.180
weeks.

01:15:10.740 --> 01:15:11.620
Sirius is the

01:15:11.620 --> 01:15:12.620
brightest star in

01:15:12.620 --> 01:15:13.360
the night sky,

01:15:14.040 --> 01:15:14.920
so if this was an

01:15:14.920 --> 01:15:15.940
espionage satellite,

01:15:16.160 --> 01:15:16.820
they weren't doing

01:15:16.820 --> 01:15:17.740
a great job of

01:15:17.740 --> 01:15:18.280
hiding it.

01:15:18.960 --> 01:15:19.700
Corona satellites

01:15:19.700 --> 01:15:20.480
were deliberately

01:15:20.480 --> 01:15:21.420
built with less

01:15:21.420 --> 01:15:22.560
reflective materials

01:15:22.560 --> 01:15:23.500
than others at

01:15:23.500 --> 01:15:24.000
the time,

01:15:24.340 --> 01:15:25.480
making it extremely

01:15:25.480 --> 01:15:26.620
incompatible with

01:15:26.620 --> 01:15:27.260
the exceptional

01:15:27.260 --> 01:15:28.120
brightness that

01:15:28.120 --> 01:15:28.960
Jacques reports.

01:15:29.380 --> 01:15:30.020
Jacques also

01:15:30.020 --> 01:15:30.720
mentioned that the

01:15:30.720 --> 01:15:31.820
object did not

01:15:31.820 --> 01:15:33.000
reappear in successive

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:34.740
weeks, also strange

01:15:34.740 --> 01:15:35.760
and inconsistent with

01:15:35.760 --> 01:15:36.680
the corona satellite

01:15:36.680 --> 01:15:37.340
explanation.

01:15:37.980 --> 01:15:39.040
What happened next

01:15:39.040 --> 01:15:40.140
would shock young

01:15:40.140 --> 01:15:41.240
Jacques to his very

01:15:41.240 --> 01:15:41.640
core.

01:15:42.200 --> 01:15:43.340
His superior at the

01:15:43.340 --> 01:15:44.340
observatory, Paul

01:15:44.340 --> 01:15:45.580
Muller, got a hold

01:15:45.580 --> 01:15:46.240
of the data.

01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:47.300
The next morning,

01:15:47.500 --> 01:15:48.500
Muller, who behaved

01:15:48.500 --> 01:15:49.440
like a petty army

01:15:49.440 --> 01:15:50.620
officer, simply

01:15:50.620 --> 01:15:51.880
confiscated the tape

01:15:51.880 --> 01:15:52.840
and destroyed it.

01:15:53.120 --> 01:15:53.840
Jacques would later

01:15:53.840 --> 01:15:55.300
recount realizing that

01:15:55.300 --> 01:15:56.740
scientists were human

01:15:56.740 --> 01:15:57.940
beings like the rest of

01:15:57.940 --> 01:15:58.200
us.

01:15:58.520 --> 01:15:59.540
When their reputations

01:15:59.540 --> 01:16:00.160
were threatened,

01:16:00.580 --> 01:16:01.260
when their ideas

01:16:01.260 --> 01:16:02.000
were challenged,

01:16:02.240 --> 01:16:03.260
they reacted by

01:16:03.260 --> 01:16:04.420
eliminating the data.

01:16:04.740 --> 01:16:05.600
If the data didn't

01:16:05.600 --> 01:16:06.680
fit their preconceived

01:16:06.680 --> 01:16:07.940
notions, they just

01:16:07.940 --> 01:16:08.640
got rid of it.

01:16:09.020 --> 01:16:10.620
In many ways, this was

01:16:10.620 --> 01:16:11.720
the inciting incident

01:16:11.720 --> 01:16:12.960
which sent Jacques on

01:16:12.960 --> 01:16:14.300
his lifelong hero's

01:16:14.300 --> 01:16:15.240
journey to the

01:16:15.240 --> 01:16:16.520
furthest edges of the

01:16:16.520 --> 01:16:17.200
unexplained.

01:16:17.620 --> 01:16:19.220
It also parallels the

01:16:19.220 --> 01:16:20.080
heated response

01:16:20.080 --> 01:16:21.320
Beatrice now faces

01:16:21.320 --> 01:16:22.680
from many of her peers,

01:16:22.680 --> 01:16:23.900
and it shows that her

01:16:23.900 --> 01:16:25.100
anomalous observations

01:16:25.100 --> 01:16:26.460
are in good company.

01:16:26.880 --> 01:16:28.140
They don't exist in a

01:16:28.140 --> 01:16:28.520
vacuum.

01:16:31.140 --> 01:16:32.820
Do you feel like the

01:16:32.820 --> 01:16:33.800
world is ready to

01:16:33.800 --> 01:16:34.540
accept this?

01:16:36.800 --> 01:16:38.940
I think there is no

01:16:38.940 --> 01:16:39.580
such moment.

01:16:39.700 --> 01:16:40.460
It just happens when

01:16:40.460 --> 01:16:40.920
it happens.

01:16:41.100 --> 01:16:41.120
Yeah.

01:16:41.580 --> 01:16:42.540
On the other hand,

01:16:42.580 --> 01:16:43.200
like you say,

01:16:43.820 --> 01:16:45.160
sometimes some knowledge

01:16:45.160 --> 01:16:46.320
doesn't land well because

01:16:46.320 --> 01:16:47.080
it came in the wrong

01:16:47.080 --> 01:16:47.560
moments.

01:16:47.900 --> 01:16:48.740
I don't know.

01:16:48.740 --> 01:16:50.060
But now we have all

01:16:50.060 --> 01:16:51.060
the whistleblowers

01:16:51.060 --> 01:16:52.540
coming out, or that

01:16:52.540 --> 01:16:53.540
they came out and they

01:16:53.540 --> 01:16:54.440
gave really great

01:16:54.440 --> 01:16:55.380
testimonies, all these

01:16:55.380 --> 01:16:57.040
people who have

01:16:57.040 --> 01:16:58.280
talked about their

01:16:58.280 --> 01:16:58.800
experiences.

01:16:59.000 --> 01:16:59.580
Many of them are

01:16:59.580 --> 01:17:00.320
really, really

01:17:00.320 --> 01:17:03.920
like, really, really

01:17:03.920 --> 01:17:05.240
intelligent, brilliant,

01:17:05.620 --> 01:17:06.840
healthy in all ways.

01:17:07.000 --> 01:17:07.260
Yes.

01:17:07.620 --> 01:17:08.440
And it's like people

01:17:08.440 --> 01:17:09.620
who want, like,

01:17:10.480 --> 01:17:11.500
role model people.

01:17:12.140 --> 01:17:13.080
No, we're getting to,

01:17:13.160 --> 01:17:13.760
I think, a tipping

01:17:13.760 --> 01:17:14.100
point.

01:17:14.220 --> 01:17:15.480
Even on my little

01:17:15.480 --> 01:17:16.400
YouTube show, you

01:17:16.400 --> 01:17:17.140
know, it's like we've

01:17:17.140 --> 01:17:19.240
probably broken maybe

01:17:19.240 --> 01:17:20.780
15, 16 of these

01:17:20.780 --> 01:17:22.040
people with, again,

01:17:22.040 --> 01:17:22.980
the intersection of

01:17:22.980 --> 01:17:23.640
very credible

01:17:23.640 --> 01:17:25.320
backgrounds, Green

01:17:25.320 --> 01:17:26.940
Berets, Air Force

01:17:26.940 --> 01:17:27.920
Combat Control

01:17:27.920 --> 01:17:29.400
recruits, National

01:17:29.400 --> 01:17:30.700
Geospatial Agency,

01:17:31.360 --> 01:17:32.520
elder statesman,

01:17:32.700 --> 01:17:33.400
advisor to the

01:17:33.400 --> 01:17:34.380
president, in the case

01:17:34.380 --> 01:17:35.400
of Harold Malmgren.

01:17:35.940 --> 01:17:36.580
You have all these

01:17:36.580 --> 01:17:37.880
people saying the

01:17:37.880 --> 01:17:38.520
same thing.

01:17:38.600 --> 01:17:39.680
I just interviewed a

01:17:39.680 --> 01:17:42.260
chief of aerospace

01:17:42.260 --> 01:17:43.440
medicine, you know,

01:17:43.460 --> 01:17:44.040
one of the top

01:17:44.040 --> 01:17:44.460
doctors.

01:17:44.560 --> 01:17:45.240
He was attached to

01:17:45.240 --> 01:17:45.540
NASA.

01:17:45.740 --> 01:17:46.620
He was at the Air

01:17:46.620 --> 01:17:46.880
Force.

01:17:46.960 --> 01:17:47.580
He was a senior

01:17:47.580 --> 01:17:48.260
doctor there.

01:17:48.260 --> 01:17:49.620
And he saw

01:17:49.620 --> 01:17:50.060
something.

01:17:50.960 --> 01:17:51.480
So it's like,

01:17:51.860 --> 01:17:53.220
we're getting to a

01:17:53.220 --> 01:17:53.880
tipping point, I

01:17:53.880 --> 01:17:54.400
think, where it's

01:17:54.400 --> 01:17:56.020
like, okay, one

01:17:56.020 --> 01:17:56.460
thing is a

01:17:56.460 --> 01:17:57.580
campfire story, but

01:17:57.580 --> 01:17:58.520
like, you know,

01:17:59.140 --> 01:17:59.540
a hundred?

01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:00.780
Like, how do you

01:18:00.780 --> 01:18:01.600
explain that away?

01:18:01.740 --> 01:18:02.760
I mean, it starts to

01:18:02.760 --> 01:18:03.140
get really

01:18:03.140 --> 01:18:03.500
interesting.

01:18:04.080 --> 01:18:05.180
I mean, if I look

01:18:05.180 --> 01:18:06.020
at everything that I

01:18:06.020 --> 01:18:06.700
learned in the last

01:18:06.700 --> 01:18:08.980
years, I will be

01:18:08.980 --> 01:18:09.180
fair.

01:18:09.260 --> 01:18:09.960
I don't think we are

01:18:09.960 --> 01:18:10.280
alone.

01:18:10.540 --> 01:18:11.000
I think we have

01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:11.420
company.

01:18:12.420 --> 01:18:13.780
And that's my

01:18:13.780 --> 01:18:14.240
impression.

01:18:14.880 --> 01:18:15.780
I'm hopelessly

01:18:15.780 --> 01:18:16.260
curious.

01:18:16.260 --> 01:18:18.960
And I cannot, I

01:18:18.960 --> 01:18:20.480
cannot stop once I, I

01:18:20.480 --> 01:18:21.380
mean, once you see

01:18:21.380 --> 01:18:22.320
these kind of results,

01:18:22.460 --> 01:18:23.900
it's not like you can

01:18:23.900 --> 01:18:24.940
just give up and say,

01:18:25.040 --> 01:18:25.860
no, no, I, you

01:18:25.860 --> 01:18:28.420
know, I should go and

01:18:28.420 --> 01:18:29.460
do some classical

01:18:29.460 --> 01:18:30.580
astronomy to support

01:18:30.580 --> 01:18:31.120
my living.

01:18:31.320 --> 01:18:32.220
You just can't.

01:18:32.260 --> 01:18:32.820
It's also like

01:18:32.820 --> 01:18:33.540
something you become

01:18:33.540 --> 01:18:34.360
dependent on.

01:18:34.540 --> 01:18:34.780
Yeah.

01:18:34.880 --> 01:18:35.640
Trying to satisfy

01:18:35.640 --> 01:18:36.700
that curiosity, ask a

01:18:36.700 --> 01:18:37.320
new question, you

01:18:37.320 --> 01:18:37.980
have to know.

01:18:38.560 --> 01:18:39.420
I think it's just

01:18:39.420 --> 01:18:40.580
going to take time for

01:18:40.580 --> 01:18:41.400
this to get out

01:18:41.400 --> 01:18:41.700
there.

01:18:41.840 --> 01:18:42.760
I think when people

01:18:42.760 --> 01:18:43.800
actually see this

01:18:43.800 --> 01:18:45.480
published and read

01:18:45.480 --> 01:18:46.240
it, I think it's

01:18:47.120 --> 01:18:48.200
if they think about

01:18:48.200 --> 01:18:48.780
it, I think they're

01:18:48.780 --> 01:18:49.360
going to be very

01:18:49.360 --> 01:18:50.500
intrigued by this.

01:18:50.640 --> 01:18:51.140
So it's going to be

01:18:51.140 --> 01:18:52.420
interesting to see

01:18:52.420 --> 01:18:53.800
what, if anything,

01:18:54.420 --> 01:18:55.820
this changes in terms

01:18:55.820 --> 01:18:56.920
of the way people

01:18:56.920 --> 01:18:58.040
think about science

01:18:58.040 --> 01:18:58.600
of UAP.

01:18:59.100 --> 01:19:00.200
But I know there

01:19:00.200 --> 01:19:01.040
are many other

01:19:01.040 --> 01:19:02.520
interesting scientific

01:19:02.520 --> 01:19:03.840
projects going on

01:19:03.840 --> 01:19:05.640
in the UAP area.

01:19:05.840 --> 01:19:06.540
And I think in the

01:19:06.540 --> 01:19:07.120
next, you know,

01:19:07.160 --> 01:19:08.140
five or ten years,

01:19:08.240 --> 01:19:09.000
it's going to be

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:10.760
night and day from

01:19:10.760 --> 01:19:11.700
what it has been in

01:19:11.700 --> 01:19:12.180
the past.

01:19:12.220 --> 01:19:12.600
And we're going to

01:19:12.600 --> 01:19:13.600
start seeing a lot

01:19:13.600 --> 01:19:15.200
more peer-reviewed

01:19:15.200 --> 01:19:17.240
studies, assuming

01:19:17.240 --> 01:19:18.020
journals are willing

01:19:18.020 --> 01:19:18.680
to take them.

01:19:18.940 --> 01:19:19.540
That's always the

01:19:19.540 --> 01:19:20.840
concern, is because

01:19:20.840 --> 01:19:22.120
of the topic, a lot

01:19:22.120 --> 01:19:22.740
of journals don't

01:19:22.740 --> 01:19:23.420
even want to touch

01:19:23.420 --> 01:19:23.600
it.

01:19:23.600 --> 01:19:29.760
We've spent most of

01:19:29.760 --> 01:19:30.900
this episode examining

01:19:30.900 --> 01:19:32.120
the data, but with

01:19:32.120 --> 01:19:33.100
results that so

01:19:33.100 --> 01:19:34.280
thoroughly challenge our

01:19:34.280 --> 01:19:35.580
existing modalities and

01:19:35.580 --> 01:19:36.820
worldviews, it's worth

01:19:36.820 --> 01:19:38.120
stepping back and trying

01:19:38.120 --> 01:19:39.200
to grasp at a bigger

01:19:39.200 --> 01:19:39.640
picture.

01:19:40.180 --> 01:19:41.360
So what does all of

01:19:41.360 --> 01:19:42.540
this mean, and what

01:19:42.540 --> 01:19:43.160
are the deeper

01:19:43.160 --> 01:19:43.760
implications?

01:19:44.500 --> 01:19:45.780
As with any cosmic

01:19:45.780 --> 01:19:46.980
shift in perspective,

01:19:47.500 --> 01:19:48.860
Carl Sagan's pale blue

01:19:48.860 --> 01:19:50.060
dot comes to mind.

01:19:50.060 --> 01:19:52.380
Our imagined self

01:19:52.380 --> 01:19:53.680
importance, the

01:19:53.680 --> 01:19:54.660
delusion that we have

01:19:54.660 --> 01:19:56.220
some privileged position

01:19:56.220 --> 01:19:57.780
in the universe, are

01:19:57.780 --> 01:19:58.460
challenged.

01:19:59.040 --> 01:20:00.360
But what does this all

01:20:00.360 --> 01:20:01.600
mean if our pale blue

01:20:01.600 --> 01:20:02.880
dot is being intently

01:20:02.880 --> 01:20:04.040
studied by other

01:20:04.040 --> 01:20:05.240
little pale dots?

01:20:05.760 --> 01:20:07.080
Pale dots that fully

01:20:07.080 --> 01:20:07.840
surround it.

01:20:08.060 --> 01:20:09.160
What new meanings do

01:20:09.160 --> 01:20:10.640
Sagan's words carry if

01:20:10.640 --> 01:20:11.900
we're actually not a

01:20:11.900 --> 01:20:12.860
lonely and obscure

01:20:12.860 --> 01:20:15.000
speck, but instead so

01:20:15.000 --> 01:20:16.280
enveloped in cosmic

01:20:16.280 --> 01:20:18.120
company that tens of

01:20:18.120 --> 01:20:19.200
thousands of alien

01:20:19.200 --> 01:20:20.500
satellites were studying

01:20:20.500 --> 01:20:22.160
our planet before we

01:20:22.160 --> 01:20:23.400
could even launch one

01:20:23.400 --> 01:20:23.940
of our own?

01:20:24.380 --> 01:20:25.800
I can't answer that in

01:20:25.800 --> 01:20:27.160
this video, but maybe

01:20:27.160 --> 01:20:28.300
trying to contemplate

01:20:28.300 --> 01:20:29.440
those questions is a

01:20:29.440 --> 01:20:30.420
next step in our

01:20:30.420 --> 01:20:31.440
collective evolution.

01:20:31.960 --> 01:20:32.760
And if you ever do

01:20:32.760 --> 01:20:34.280
find yourself staring up

01:20:34.280 --> 01:20:35.420
and watching a starry

01:20:35.420 --> 01:20:37.160
night sky, just ask

